            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">What is the maximum age for a financed caravan?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">This varies by lender. Most will finance caravans up to 15–20 years old at the end of the loan term. For example, if a lender has a 20-year maximum and you take a 7-year loan, the caravan can be up to 13 years old at the time of purchase. Some specialist lenders are more flexible with age limits for well-maintained caravans from reputable brands. Motorhomes, being registered vehicles, sometimes have different age limits.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Do I need a deposit for caravan finance?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Most lenders do not require a deposit for new caravan purchases by borrowers with strong credit. For used caravans, a deposit of 10–20% can improve approval chances and secure a better rate — particularly for older units or if your credit is not perfect. A deposit also protects against negative equity if the caravan depreciates.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Can I get caravan finance with bad credit?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Yes, though options are more limited. Specialist lenders may approve caravan finance for borrowers with impaired credit, particularly if the caravan is a newer model with strong resale value and you have a deposit. Rates will be higher than standard (typically 12–20% p.a.). Nik Finance can identify which specialist lenders are most likely to approve your application.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">How long can I finance a caravan for?</h3>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Finance terms for caravans and motorhomes can extend up to 7–10 years with some lenders, particularly for higher-value units. Longer terms keep monthly repayments lower but increase total interest paid. A common sweet spot is 5–7 years for most caravan purchases. Lenders may limit the term based on the age of the caravan.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
